Hyperspectral Image Classification Framework
Research Project - Hyderabad Institute of Technology and Management

Project Details:
- Author: Tirumala Manav
- Co-Author: Lalan Kumar
- Co-Author: Prof. Bhaaskar Das
- Co-Author: Prof. Dhananjoy Bhakta
- Institution: Hyderabad Institute of Technology and Management
- Contact: thirumalamanav123@gmail.com

Technical Implementation:
- HICNN: Custom CNN with multiple depth variants
- HICAE: Convolutional Autoencoder architecture
- HIC-GAN: Generative Adversarial Network implementation
- Security: Cryptographic face verification system
- Framework: PyTorch, Flask, OpenCV

Research Applications:
This framework was developed for advanced hyperspectral image classification
research with applications in remote sensing, agriculture, environmental
monitoring, and geospatial analysis.

Educational Purpose:
This project is released for educational and research purposes to advance
the field of hyperspectral image analysis and deep learning applications.
